# 1. ひとりぼっちの雨模様

Saki: Ngh... Huh?
Saki: I didn't realize I fell asleep. Ugh, my neck hurts. I must have slept in a weird position.
Saki: It's raining again... I'm fed up with rain.
Saki: I hope the weather's nicer when my family comes to visit.
Saki: ...
Saki: If it doesn't clear up, I won't see the stars tonight, either.
Saki: I wonder how everyone's doing. I wonder if they're having fun with their classmates...
Saki: I miss them so much...
Saki: Ngh...
Saki: Huh? This isn't a hospital bed...
Saki: Oh, that's right. I'm all better now!
Saki: I can see everyone again...
Tsukasa's Voice: Saki! Are you not ready yet?
Tsukasa's Voice: It's good that you've been putting so much effort into getting ready for the day each morning, but if you take too long, you'll be late!
Saki: What? It's morning? Wh-What time is it?!
Saki: Oh no... I overslept!
Saki: Huff... Huff... I... I made it...
Saki: That was close. If Tsukasa didn't wake me up, I definitely would've been late for classes.
Ichika: Morning, Saki. Glad you made it.
Ichika: You're not the type to oversleep in the mornings, so I was surprised when you messaged me. Did you stay up too late?
Saki: No, but I guess I was so caught up in my dream that I couldn't wake up.
Ichika: What sort of dream?
Saki: Well... It was, um...
Classmate: Tenma, Hoshino... The teacher's coming.
Saki: Oh, right! Thanks for the heads up!
Saki: Come on, Ichi! We should return to our seats!
Ichika: Yeah, right.
Saki: (She'd feel bad if I told her that I was dreaming about when I was in the hospital.)
Saki: (The hospital was too far for her to visit me often and I think it made her feel guilty.)
Saki: (I don't want to cause my friends any more worries now that I've gotten better.)
Saki: (Let's make the most of this day!)
Saki: Yay, time to close the textbooks and head off to practice!
Ichika: Yeah. You're really hyped today, Saki.
Saki: I guess so! I almost started off by running late today, but it's all good now!
Saki: Besides, we're meeting in you-know-where today!
Ichika: That's right. It's been a while since we last went, so I'm looking forward to it too.
Honami: Hi, Saki. Hi, Ichika.
Saki: Honami! You made it through the day, so... Lemme give you a hug!
Honami: Aaah! Careful, Saki. You almost made me fall over...!
Shiho: Don't cause a scene in the corridor.
Saki: Shiho! Don't you worry, I've got a hug for you too! Come here!
Shiho: Hey, cut it out. We've got important plans today, so let's find somewhere more private.
Honami: Shiho, maybe you shouldn't be pinching Saki's cheeks like that. Her face just looks... Hehehe.
Ichika: Haha! Saki, you should see yourself!
Saki: I pwomise I won't twy to hug you anymwore, fo let gwo of my sheeks!
Ichika: Looks like no one's around. Are you all ready?
Saki: Yeah!
Ichika: Okay... Here we go!
Miku: Welcome back!
Luka: Hehe. We've been waiting for you.
Saki: Miku! Luka! Thanks for having us!
Miku: Always happy to. I see you're full of pep as always, Saki.
Ichika: And yet, this morning she surprised us by almost turning up late for classes.
Shiho: What, really? That's pretty unusual.
Honami: You always come to school so early. Did something happen?
Saki: Hehe... I fell back asleep right after waking up.
Shiho: Haha, THAT is just like you.
Saki: Anyways, enough about that. I can't wait to show the fruits of our labor to Miku and Luka!
Ichika: Okay, let's get ready to play.
Honami & Shiho: Yeah!
Saki: (That dream really startled me, but I'm fine now.)
Saki: (I'm no longer all alone. I'm with my friends.)
Saki: (I have to make up for the time I lost from here on out!)
